section.section:
This subsection applies to an individual who on June 30, 2004, receives an annual salary and who is:
an elected or appointed official;
an employee of the Governor's office;
an employee of the Senate or House of Delegates;
a member of the Prince George's County Board of License Commissioners; or
an employee of Dorchester County who is not a member of the county's general pension and retirement program.

Membership in the Employees' Pension System is not optional for individuals who are:
supportive service employees of the Board of Education of Kent County;
employees of the Town of Oakland;
employees of the City of Frostburg;
employees of the Town of Sykesville; or
employees of the Town of University Park.
